The lax vowels [I], [Y], [U], and [O] have the tense variants [i], [y], [u], and [o]. The distribution of lax and tense vowels is not entirely clear. There is a tendency for stressed and/or long vowels to be tense (11).

The lax vowels [I], [Y], [U], and [O] have the tense variants [i], [y], [u], and [o]. The distribution of lax and tense vowels is not entirely clear. There is a tendency for stressed and/or long vowels to be tense (11).

The vowel /ü/ has only been preserved by some older speakers. Younger speakers replace /ü/ with /i/ or very occasionally with /u/.
